    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-10-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-10-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="327"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                <head>327. Gilpatric’s handwritten notes of meeting, October 17<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d327fn1">Preferred course of action. Top Secret. 1 p.
                            <gloss target="#t_WNRC_1">WNRC</gloss>, RG 330, <gloss
                            target="#t_OASD_1">OASD</gloss> (C) A Files: <gloss target="#t_FRC_1"
                            >FRC</gloss> 71 A 2896, RLG’s Notes <gloss target="#t_re_1">re</gloss>
                        Cuba.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-10-17">October 17, 1962</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d327-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d327-1"/>
                <p>RLG’s</p>
                <p>Preferred Course of Action</p>
                <p>1) Letters to K&amp;C protesting <gloss target="#t_MRBM_1">MRBMs</gloss> and
                    declaring that workers removed at once (with satisfactory proof). U.S. will act
                    to protest [?] against threat to its security.</p>
                <pb facs="1224" n="1049" type="typeset" xml:id="pg_1049"/>
                <p>2) Absent satisfactory response to letters by [unclear] certain. U.S.
                    government:</p>
                <quote>
                    <p>a) declares state of war with Cuba, acting under existing Cong. resol.</p>
                    <p>b) establishes blockade against all vessels entering Cuban ports</p>
                    <p>c) calls upon <gloss target="#t_OAS_1">OAS</gloss> to take complementary
                        action in defense of West. Hem. under Rio Treaty</p>
                    <p>d) notifies <gloss target="#t_UN_1">UN</gloss> of action taken in self
                        defense</p>
                    <p>e) asks <gloss target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss> allies for cooperation in
                        blockade</p>
                </quote>
                <p>3) Concurrently with 2) U.S.:</p>
                <quote>
                    <p>a) announces open and comprehensive air &amp; sea surveillance of Cuba</p>
                    <p>b) alerts forces for air strikes against Cuban military targets in event Cuba
                        moves militarily vs U.S. and prepare [unclear] for possible invasion</p>
                    <p>c) establishes air &amp; sea defense for S.E. U.S. for possible invasion.</p>
                    <p>d) evacuate dependents from Guantanamo and strengthen latter’s defensive
                        position.</p>
                    <p>e) alerts overseas forces against possible Soviet or [unclear] aggressive
                        acts</p>
                </quote>
            </div>
        </body>
